{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Cleaning & Lowercasing Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Text cleaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of removing noise and normalising raw text before it reaches a tokenizer or model. Raw text from the web, documents, or user input contains HTML tags, emoji, URLs, inconsistent casing, extra whitespace, and encoding artefacts — none of which carry the linguistic signal the model needs, and some of which cause the tokenizer to produce surprising or inconsistent token sequences."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lowercasing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is one specific cleaning step: converting all characters to lower case so that "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"NLP\""}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"nlp\""}, {"type": "text", "text": ", and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"Nlp\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " map to the same token. Whether to lowercase depends entirely on which model you are using."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Cleaning Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Problem in raw text"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Effect on the model"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "HTML tags ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<b>"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "&amp;"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tags tokenize into many tokens, diluting signal and wasting context window"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "URLs ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "https://very-long-url.com/path?q=1"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One URL can consume 20–50 tokens and teach the model nothing useful"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inconsistent casing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Word-level and uncased tokenizers treat "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"Bank\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"bank\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " as different tokens; model learns each separately"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Duplicate whitespace / \\n\\n\\n"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tokenizers can produce many padding-like tokens from repeated spaces"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Encoding errors (â€™ for ')"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Corrupted characters create rare, meaningless tokens the model has never seen at scale"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Cleaning Pipeline"}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Text cleaning pipeline: raw text passes through HTML removal, URL removal, lowercasing, and punctuation stripping to produce clean output"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1 — Remove HTML and markup"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Web-scraped text is littered with tags. Strip them before anything else, or they will be tokenized as literal angle-bracket sequences."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import re\n\ndef remove_html(text: str) -> str:\n    # Remove all <tag> and </tag> constructs\n    text = re.sub(r\"<[^>]+>\", \" \", text)\n    # Decode common HTML entities\n    text = text.replace(\"&amp;\", \"&\").replace(\"&lt;\", \"<\").replace(\"&gt;\", \">\")\n    text = text.replace(\"&nbsp;\", \" \").replace(\"&quot;\", '\"')\n    return text\n\nprint(remove_html(\"<b>Hello</b> &amp; <i>World</i>\"))\n# Hello &  World"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2 — Remove URLs and email addresses"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def remove_urls(text: str) -> str:\n    text = re.sub(r\"https?://\\S+|www\\.\\S+\", \"\", text)\n    text = re.sub(r\"\\S+@\\S+\\.\\S+\", \"\", text)   # email\n    return text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3 — Lowercase (conditionally)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "text = text.lower()   # safe for uncased models only — see the section below"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4 — Remove punctuation and special characters"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How aggressively to clean depends on the task. Classification tasks can usually drop all non-alphanumeric characters. NER or summarisation tasks must preserve punctuation because sentence boundaries carry meaning."}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def remove_punctuation(text: str) -> str:\n    # Keep letters, digits, and whitespace; strip everything else\n    return re.sub(r\"[^a-z0-9\\s]\", \"\", text)\n\n# Alternative: keep punctuation but normalise repeated marks\ndef normalise_punctuation(text: str) -> str:\n    text = re.sub(r\"[!]{2,}\", \"!\", text)   # !!! → !\n    text = re.sub(r\"[.]{3,}\", \"...\", text)  # ..... → ...\n    return text"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5 — Normalise whitespace"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def normalise_whitespace(text: str) -> str:\n    return \" \".join(text.split())   # collapses \\t, \\n, multiple spaces"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Full pipeline"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def clean_text(text: str, lowercase: bool = True) -> str:\n    text = remove_html(text)\n    text = remove_urls(text)\n    if lowercase:\n        text = text.lower()\n    text = remove_punctuation(text)\n    text = normalise_whitespace(text)\n    return text.strip()\n\nraw = \"<b>AI News!</b> Visit https://ai.example.com 😊 Phone: +1(555)123-4567\"\nprint(clean_text(raw))\n# ai news  phone 15551234567"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowercasing: When to Apply and When to Skip"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowercasing is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "not universally correct"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". It depends on how the model's tokenizer was trained:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Tokenizer type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowercase before tokenizing?"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BERT-uncased, DistilBERT"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece, lowercased vocab"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Yes — tokenizer does it automatically"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (do_lower_case=True)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "BERT-cased, RoBERTa"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "WordPiece, case-sensitive"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No — case carries semantic information"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "GPT-2, GPT-4, Llama"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Byte-BPE / tiktoken"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No — \"The\" and \"the\" are different tokens"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Classic ML (TF-IDF, bag-of-words)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Word-level"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Yes — reduces vocabulary size significantly"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Rule of thumb:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " if the model name ends in "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "-uncased"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", the tokenizer lowercases for you — you can leave the text as-is. If the model is cased (or a causal LM like GPT/Llama), do not lowercase: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"NASA\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"nasa\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " are meaningfully different tokens."}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Handling Unicode and Encoding Issues"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Text scraped from the web often has encoding problems — Windows-1252 read as UTF-8 produces artefacts like "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "â€™"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for the right-single-quote "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "'"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "ftfy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " library fixes these reliably:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install ftfy\nimport ftfy\n\nbad = \"I canâ€™t believe itâ€™s not butter\"\nprint(ftfy.fix_text(bad))\n# I can't believe it's not butter\n\n# Also useful: normalise Unicode to NFC (composed form)\nimport unicodedata\ntext = unicodedata.normalize(\"NFC\", text)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Not to Remove"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aggressive cleaning can hurt model performance. Avoid stripping:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sentence-ending punctuation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " ("}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": ". ! ?"}, {"type": "text", "text": ") when the task involves understanding sentence boundaries"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Numbers"}, {"type": "text", "text": " when the task is numeric reasoning, finance, or date extraction"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Domain-specific symbols"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — in code, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "{ } ( ) ;"}, {"type": "text", "text": " are essential; in chemistry, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "C=O"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is meaningful"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Named entities"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — lowercasing "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"Python\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " (the language) also changes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "\"python\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " (the snake); cased models handle the distinction automatically"}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using spaCy for Production Cleaning"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For production pipelines, spaCy handles cleaning, sentence splitting, and token normalisation together:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# pip install spacy && python -m spacy download en_core_web_sm\nimport spacy\n\nnlp = spacy.load(\"en_core_web_sm\")\n\ndef clean_with_spacy(text: str) -> str:\n    doc = nlp(text)\n    tokens = [\n        token.text.lower()\n        for token in doc\n        if not token.is_space          # skip whitespace tokens\n        and not token.like_url         # skip URLs\n        and not token.like_email       # skip emails\n        and not token.is_punct         # skip punctuation (remove for NER)\n    ]\n    return \" \".join(tokens)\n\nprint(clean_with_spacy(\"Visit https://spacy.io — it's great!\"))\n# visit it 's great"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Cleaning Strategy by Task"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Task"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Remove HTML"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Remove URLs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Lowercase"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Strip punct"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sentiment classification"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If uncased model"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optional"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NER / entity extraction"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No — case identifies proper nouns"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No — keep sentence boundaries"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLM pre-training data"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sometimes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No — preserve natural casing"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "TF-IDF / bag-of-words"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Yes — reduces sparsity"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Yes"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Text cleaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": " removes noise (HTML, URLs, encoding errors, extra whitespace) that wastes context window and produces rare or meaningless tokens"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Lowercasing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " unifies variant spellings for uncased models but "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "must be skipped for cased models"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (GPT, BERT-cased, Llama) where capitalisation encodes meaning"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apply HTML removal "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "before"}, {"type": "text", "text": " tokenization — otherwise "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<b>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " becomes literal angle-bracket tokens"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "ftfy.fix_text()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to repair encoding artefacts from charset mis-detection before any other step"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Do not over-clean"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": punctuation, numbers, and casing carry signal for many downstream tasks — strip only what you know hurts your specific task"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The cleaning strategy is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "task-specific"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": NER and summarisation need punctuation and casing; classification and TF-IDF benefit from aggressive normalisation"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Transformer-based pipelines, the tokenizer's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "do_lower_case"}, {"type": "text", "text": " flag controls lowercasing automatically — prefer letting the tokenizer handle it rather than lowercasing in a separate step"}]}]}]}]}}